						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Sāyaṇa-uḍaiyār Year: 9.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records that some <hi rend="italic">agambaḍiyārs</hi> of Paḍuvūr, Kāliṅgarāyaṉ, Sēdirāyaṉ, Ādittaṉ and Kāyavaḍugaṉ resided in the village and protected it for a long time. But for reasons not known they neglected their duty and wrought havoc in the village. Probably their lands were taken over and donated it to the temple as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi.</hi> Other details are not clear.</p>						

						<p>This inscription on the grounds of palaeography may be assigned to the 14-15th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
